Tag someone who should try this 😊. 
Bored of Red or White Sauce Pasta? Try this easy peasy Pink Sauce Pasta right away 💕. 
I definitely like this better than the other two. 
Process: 
1. Boil and strain 1 cup Pasta. Save some of this water. 
2. Heat butter and oil in a Pan. Saute some garlic for 2-3 mins. Next add Onion, corn and capsicum and fry for 4-5 mins. 
3. Now add tomato puree , red chilli powder, salt, pepper, oregano, chilli flakes and mix well. Cook till the tomato puree condenses. Might take about 7-8 mins.
4. Add the Pasta water saves in step 1. Now add the Boiled Pasta and mix till the gravy gets coated. 
5. Pour fresh cream, some cheese and parsley and mix. 
Serve with some toasted Bread and enjoy Hot 😋😋.

Looking for another high protein breakfast recipe? Comment “Chilla” and I’ll send you my stuffed Besan Chilla recipe with 27g protein. 

Macros: 410 cal, 26g Protein

🥪 Blend together 60g Low fat paneer, 1/2 cheese slice, 100ml skim milk into a smooth paste. Add little water if needed.

🥪 Add 1/2 tsp each oregano, chilli flakes, salt, 1 tsp honey and mix well.

🥪 Toast two slices of 100% whole wheat bread with a little bit of butter until crispy. Spread a generous amount of the prepared cheese spread and top with slices cucumbers. 

🥪 Sprinkle some sesame seeds and chilli flakes. Serve with the remaining cheese spread!

Andhra Style Crispy Potato Fry : perfect side dish with Rice and Sambar 🤩❤️. 
1. Peel and slice 750g potato into slices . Cut them into vertical strips and wash twice with water. Drain off excess water and transfer to a bowl. 
2. Add 1.5 tsp Red Chilli powder, 1 tsp pepper, 1.5 tsp Garam masala, 2 tsp chaat masala, 2tbsp cornflour, 2tbsp rice flour, salt and mix well. 
3. Drop into slightly warm oil and deep fry on high flame until crispy. Deep fry curry leaves . Sprinkle chaat masala when hot and mix well. Serve immediately with rice and sambar 🥰❤️.

Mysore masala dosa for all the spice lovers 😍🫶. 
Save the reel to try it later.

1. In a bowl take 6 Byadgi chilli, 2 Guntur chilli and lemon sized tamarind. Pour hot water and let it rest for 20 mins. 
2. Sauté 1 onion , 5-6 garlic cloves and transfer everything into a mixer jar. Add 1 tbsp roasted chana dal, 2 tbsp coconut chunks, salt and the water in which chillies were soaked. Blend smoothly into a thick paste. 
3. Spread dosa batter on a cast iron tawa which is slightly hot. Put some oil and then spread a good amount of the red chutney on it. Once dosa is nicely browned add the aloo Palya, chopped onions and coriander. 
Fold and serve immediately with any chutney of choice 🥰♥️♥️. 

Do try it out and send me your feedback pictures.

Healthy munching snack : Air fried Namkeen with the goodness of @uscranberriesin. 

Cranberries are one of the healthiest fruits and you can buy them from any major e-commerce platform or a leading dry fruit store ✨

1. Toss in 1 cup makhana, 1 cup murmura, 1/2 cup rolled oats, 1/2 cup roasted Chana dal, 1/4 cup pumpkin seeds. Place a mesh plate on top and air fry at 185 C for 12 mins shaking midway. 
2. ⁠Heat 2 tbsp ghee and fry peanuts. Add 1.5 tbsp amchur, 1 tsp turmeric, 1/2 tsp red chilli, salt, curry leaves and mix. Add this to the namkeen along with 1/2 cup @uscranberriesin. 
3. ⁠Mix everything well and store in an airtight jar!
#thecranberryinstitute #cranberries #cranberrydelights #benefitsofcranberries #cranberriesinindia

Nepali Chukauni that’s ready in just 5mins and is so so comforting. This is Episode 3 of #KeepCoolWithVaishali 🍹🧊

1. Whisk 400g curd with salt and 2-3tbsp water. Add 1 sliced onion, 1-2 boiled and diced  potato, 1 chopped green chilli and coriander leaves. Mix everything well. 
2. Heat mustard oil nicely and add 1/2 tsp cumin, 1/4tsp methi seeds, 1/4 tsp turmeric, 1/4 tsp red chilli powder, 1/4 tsp kasuri methi and red chilli. Mix and add the tadka to the curd mixture. Mix and serve with rice! 

Do try and send me your feedback pictures.
